visa information's visa_name - Electronic Travel Authority (Subclass 601)

visa information's description - The Electronic Travel Authority (Subclass 601) is a temporary visa that allows holders to visit Australia for tourism or business visitor activities for up to 3 months at a time within a 12-month period.

visa information's eligibility - ['Must hold a valid passport from an eligible country.', 'Cannot apply with a non-citizen passport, certificate of identity, or other travel document.', 'Must not have a criminal conviction in any country.', 'Must meet health and character requirements.']

visa information's benefits - ['Travel to Australia multiple times within the visa validity period.', 'Stay in Australia for up to 3 months on each entry.', 'Study or train for up to 3 months in total.']
visa information's obligations - ['Must meet all visa conditions and obey Australian laws.', 'Cannot undertake paid work for an Australian employer.', 'Must leave Australia before the visa expires.']
visa information's cost - ['No Visa Application Charge (VAC).', 'AUD20 service charge to use the Australian ETA app.']
visa information's processing_times - ['In most cases, notified immediately of the result.', 'May take longer if additional information is required.']
visa information's apply_from - ['Must be outside Australia when applying and when the visa is granted.']
visa information's apply_outside_australia - ['Apply using the Australian ETA app.', 'Travel industry representatives can assist with the application.']
visa information's family_inclusion - ['Cannot include family members in the application.', 'Each family member must submit a separate application.']
visa information's travel_rights - ['Multiple entries allowed while the visa is valid.', 'Can leave and re-enter Australia as many times as desired within the visa validity.']
visa information's stay_duration - ['Up to 3 months on each entry.']
visa information's health_requirements - ['Must meet health requirements.', 'If entering healthcare or hospital environments, apply for a Visitor (subclass 600) visa.']
visa information's health_insurance - Recommended to take out health insurance to cover unforeseen medical treatment.
visa information's visa_label - Visa is digitally linked to the passport used for the application. No physical label is provided.
visa information's additional_info - If found not to be a genuine visitor, the ETA may be cancelled. Must declare all passports if holding more than one.
visa information's includes_children - Children cannot be included in the application; they must apply separately.
visa information's processing_requirements - ['Must provide accurate information.', 'Must have a live facial image taken if applying through an agent.']
visa information's questions_and_answers - ['Check the Frequently Asked Questions within the app for more help.', 'If ineligible for an ETA, consider applying for another visa through ImmiAccount.']
